article.headline: New Orleans 86, Troy 85
article.story: TROY, Ala. (AP) -- With a game-high 25 points, including six 3-pointers, James Parlow led New Orleans to an 86-85 victory over Troy Wednesday night. Thanks to two key turnovers in the final 1:05 and a solid defensive stand in the final seconds, the Privateers (9-10, 5-3 Sun Belt Conference) managed the win and reversed a brief two-game losing trend. Bo McCalebb was just behind Parlow with 24 points for New Orleans, while Shaun Reynolds and Jamie McNeilly added 14 and 13 points respectively. Troy (8-11, 3-5 SBC) had five double digit scorers. Richard Chaney led with 25 points. Sammy Sharp and Cedric Jackson had 13 points each. Boo Ramsey added 12 and O'Darien Bassett chipped in with 11 points and seven assists. The Trojans were ahead 83-82 with 1:30 left when the Privateers scored on back-to-back turnovers. McCalebb had a dunk with 39 seconds left, giving New Orleans an 86-83 lead. A layup by Troy's Cedric Jackson cut the lead to 86-85. After UNO missed a free throw, Troy's Sammy Sharp missed a contested reverse layup.
